The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks in image recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of JPEG compression as a pre-processing step to counter adversarial attacks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and security and privacy (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposal of an ensemble-based technique also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of image manipulation techniques and the discussion of image compression suggest a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
